The third podcast for TTS 2020.08.18's DS Course is Voting Mechanisms of Data Skeptic, a conversation with Steven Heilman discussing his paper Designing Stable Elections. This was a moderately technical, highly mathematical discussion about the various different aspects of voting systems from a data science standpoint, with a strong background of the probabilities, combinatorics, and topology involved in the mathematics of designing a robust voting mechanism.

https://open.spotify.com/episode/2ysHqrU9dEAxEg6LTWyis2?si=QDI2rFNgSLWNOGDjFiZh-w